  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT233-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">paṭṭapiṉṟai varaiyātu ceṉṟu viṉaimuṟṟi mīḷun talaimakaṉ tērppākaṟkuc
          colliyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered to the charioteer by HIM who returned after
          completing [his] work, having gone without marrying after it had become [public]. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT233">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> kavalai keṇṭiya vakalvāyc ciṟukuḻi</l>
          <l> koṉṟai yoḷvī tāayc celvar</l>
          <l> poṉpey pēḻai mūytiṟan taṉṉa</l>
          <l> kāretir puṟavi ṉatuvē yuyarntōrkku</l>
          <l> nīroṭu corinta miccil yāvarkkum</l>
          <l> varaikō ḷaṟiyāc coṉṟi</l>
          <l> niraikōṟ kuṟuntoṭi tantai yūrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>The village of the father of [her with] tight bracelets in a row</l>
          <l>[means] cooked rice that knows no limit</l>
          <l rend="indent">for anyone, as a rest of what is poured forth with water</l>
          <l rend="indent8">for high-born ones .</l>
          <l>It [lies] in the woodland, in the face of the rainy season,</l>
          <l rend="indent">as if the lid is opened of the gold-raining baskets</l>
          <l rend="indent6">of prosperous people,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">since the bright blossoms of the Laburnum are spread</l>
          <l rend="indent4">in small pits with wide mouths dug for the Kavalai plants.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
